File: Gauteng Education MEC Panyaza Lesufi. JOHANNESBURG - The Institute of Race Relations (IRR) is calling for a probe of Gauteng Education MEC Panyaza Lesufi and his department. The IRR has approached the Public Protector, citing possible maladministration and inefficient expenditure. It has raised several issues, starting with the department's website. READ: Panyaza Lesufi back as Education MEC Instead of providing access to new online curriculum lessons as it should, the website is poorly designed, the IRR said. The Institute wants allegations that the department misspent R1,2-billion investigated. READ: Lesufi says no pupil will be turned away The school placement system has also been marred by complaints. The IRR accuses Lesufi of being flippant when asked about these issues.